data.description:
3 BR 1 3/4 bathroom diamond in the rough.  Could use a few things updated and some other items fixed but the cost to do so is minimal considering the value of the home overall.  Large family room downstairs could be converted to a 4th bedroom with putting in another egress window  and closet.  AC/Furnace unit less than 3 years old(2021), brand new roof (Aug 2023), Water Heater (2017).  Washer and Dryer stay with the home.  Storage Shed in the back for working in the yard or just storage.  Upstairs you have the 2 main bedrooms (Master is facing west) and one full bath.  Downstairs you have the 3/4 bath, 1 bedroom, the family room and the laundry/storage room.  In the living room there is a pellet stove (2018) and plenty of room for ideas.  The dining room and kitchen are L shaped with a galley style kitchen.  The appliances are all under 5 years old in the kitchen.  There are 3 entrances to the home which makes it easier to access depending on what you doing.

This home would do well with a 203k FHA Loan to cover the costs of any fixing the buyer would like to do.  Seller will not assist with closing costs and are located out of state currently.  Home is priced with approximate fix up costs in mind and reflects current value minus any repairs buyer might need to fix.
data.whatILove: Centrally located close to library, schools, Mountain Home AFB, downtown shops and restaurants.  Located on a street that is one of the first to be maintained during the winter snow.  Two beautiful trees are maturing in the front yard.  Lots of natural light in the upstairs portion of the home.  Room to grow for any small family.  Large family room downstairs adds to the features of the home.  In ground sprinkler system, asian plum tree in the back yard and a clothes line during the summer and fall months.  Great neighbors and close to the hospital in town as well.
